<h3>Debian Linux packages</h3>

<p><a href="http://debian.org">Debian Linux</a> users may also benefit from
our Debian package repository. The C interface can be installed and
automatically updated using the standard Debian package manager. Just add
the following two lines to <code>/etc/apt/sources.list</code> and install
the <code>libigraph</code> and <code>libigraph-dev</code> packages:</p>

<pre>
deb http://cneurocvs.rmki.kfki.hu /packages/binary/
deb-src htp://cneurocvs.rmki.kfki.hu /packages/source/
</pre>

<p>The binary packages are built for the <code>i386</code> architecture.
Source packages should compile on <code>x86_64</code> and <code>amd64</code>
architectures as well.

<h3>Obtaining the development version</h3>

<p>You can get the latest development version of <b>igraph</b> (including the
C core and the wrappers for R and Python) with the <code>tla</code> arch
revision control system from the following URL:
<code>http://cneurocvs.rmki.kfki.hu/arch/csardi@rmki.kfki.hu--2004-public</code>.</p>
